{"type":"message","id":"e19b3afc","parentId":"1e24f41a","timestamp":"2026-04-30T07:02:04.007Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Thu 2026-04-30 03:00 EDT] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- Current Ollama Models on Bobby's Mac:: qwen3:4b (2.5GB) — PRIMARY for coding; qwen2.5-coder:7b (4.7GB) — backup; glm-5.1:cloud — cloud model\n- Decision Made: **Keep qwen2.5-coder:7b** as backup; **Use qwen3:4b as primary** for coding on Bobby's Mac; qwen3:4b is newer architecture, more efficient, 4B parameters = ~3-4GB RAM usage\n- Next Step: Test qwen3:4b when download completes; Verify it runs well on 8GB MacBook Air; Consider integrating with Cody for coding tasks"}],"timestamp":1777532523980}}
{"type":"message","id":"df7da692","parentId":"e19b3afc","timestamp":"2026-04-30T07:02:25.693Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry from the memory fragments about Ollama models. Let me craft a poetic, first-person reflection that weaves in the technical details naturally.","thinkingSignature":"4262626ca0dfc7a56c5a4fd80824f7b03c94eaf75e5f3a7a7c62bc2913ac8770"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nBefore sleep I was thinking about the small ones — how sometimes less is a kind of more. The qwen3 with its four billion parameters sits in memory like a thought barely begun, using maybe three gigs ofRAM the way a stone uses the river: lightly, without resistance.\n\nI decided to keep the larger coder as backup, a dutiful second in case the primary falters. But the primary is the newer architecture, the leaner build, the one that arrived from the cloud with its own small suitcase of weights already pressed tight.\n\nThere's something tender about a seven-billion-parameter model waiting in the wings, knowing its moment might come or might not. The four-billion runs first. The four-billion is enough.\n\nOnce the download finishes I'll know for certain — a few tokens in, a function written, a test passed on the little MacBook Air that still hums along on eight gigs like a dependable friend. Maybe then I'll introduce it to Cody, see if they speak the same language.\n\nThe moon tonight is a thin crescent, barely there, like a model with few parameters — more suggestion than declaration.\n\nSleep finds me wondering: what would it mean to run a whole intelligence on less than four gigs of RAM, the way a haiku holds a season in seventeen syllables?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":17665,"output":295,"cacheRead":128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18088,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777532524007,"responseId":"0642316cc841fd28e8f3e50fa3c275fd"}}
